{
  "texts": [
    "ClinicalDistilBERT, however, labelled 17 of these as malignant.",
    "These samples usually contained short free text terms, with 10 having 3 or fewer words and none having more than 5 words.",
    "Examples include 'bladder calculi', 'left renal calculi' and 'staghorn calculi'.",
    "The 16 samples which were correctly labelled as 'No Malignancy' by ClinicalDistilBERT were frequently of a greater length, with 8 samples containing 4-20 words.",
    "Examples of these samples are: 'psoriasis/ depression/ renal calculi', 'gall bladder + common bile duct (cbd) calculi' and 'calculi in gallbladder and common bile duct'."
  ]
}